'''Mark Maria Hubertus Flekken''' (born 13 June 1993) is a Dutch professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{German football updater|BaLeverk}} club [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]].

==Early years==
Flekken grew up in [[Bocholtz]], Limburg, Netherlands on the German border.<ref name="aachen">{{cite news |title=Aachen: Mark Flekken: Jüngste Nummer 1 in Alemannias Historie |url=https://www.aachener-zeitung.de/sport/mark-flekken-juengste-nummer-1-in-alemannias-historie_aid-26166797 |work=Aachener Zeitung |date=11 January 2013 |language=de}}</ref> His parents René and Annie used to play football themselves, and his younger brother Roy also became a goalkeeper.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Weigend |first1=David |title=SC-Freiburg-Torhüter Mark Flekken: Ich gehe auch mal gern ins Risiko |url=https://www.badische-zeitung.de/sport/scfreiburg/sc-freiburg-torhueter-mark-flekken-ich-gehe-auch-mal-gern-ins-risiko |work=Badische Zeitung |date=24 August 2020 |language=de}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Alemannia Aachen and Greuther Fürth===
Flekken started his career in the youth department of RKVV WDZ from [[Bocholtz]] before moving to the youth academy of [[Roda JC Kerkrade]]. In 2009, he moved across the border to the youth teams of the then [[2. Bundesliga]] club [[Alemannia Aachen]]. On 22 September 2011, he signed his first professional contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=Nachwuchs: Alemannia Aachen bindet Mark Flekken |url=http://www.alemannia-aachen.de/nachwuchs/nachrichten/details/Nachwuchs-Alemannia-bindet-Mark-Flekken-21000a/ |website=Alemannia Aachen |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110924131002/http://www.alemannia-aachen.de/nachwuchs/nachrichten/details/Nachwuchs-Alemannia-bindet-Mark-Flekken-21000a/ |archive-date=24 September 2011 |language=de |date=22 September 2011 |url-status=dead}}</ref>

During the winter break of the [[2012–13 3. Liga|2012–13 3. Liga season]], Flekken was appointed as the starting goalkeeper by coach [[René van Eck]] after the financially troubled club had parted ways with [[Michael Melka]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Aachen: Van Ecks nächste Stellschraube heißt Michael Melka |url=https://www.aachener-nachrichten.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/van-ecks-naechste-stellschraube-heisst-michael-melka_aid-26680333 |work=Aachener Nachrichten |date=28 September 2012 |language=de}}</ref><ref name="aachen" /> Flekken made his debut on 26 January 2013 in a 2–0 home game against [[1. FC Saarbrücken]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Alemannia Aachen vs. Saarbrücken – 26 January 2013 – Soccerway |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/01/26/germany/3-liga/alemannia-aachen/1-fc-saarbrucken-ev/1306858/ |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=23 March 2022}}</ref>

Ahead of the [[2013–14 2. Bundesliga|2013–14 season]], Flekken moved to the 2. Bundesliga club [[SpVgg Greuther Fürth]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Grün geht - Flekken kommt |url=http://www.greuther-fuerth.de/aktuell/aktuelle-news/news-detail/article/gruen-geht-flekken-kommt.html |website=SpVgg Greuther Fürth |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130607202950/http://www.greuther-fuerth.de/aktuell/aktuelle-news/news-detail/article/gruen-geht-flekken-kommt.html |archive-date=7 June 2013 |language=de |date=31 May 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> There, he only made three league appearances in three years as a backup goalkeeper behind [[Wolfgang Hesl]] and [[Sebastian Mielitz]].<ref name="DFL" />

===MSV Duisburg===
Flekken signed for [[MSV Duisburg]] on 12 June 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://msv-duisburg.de/main.asp?reiter=aktuelles_p&bgi=yes&mode=aktuell&aid=7311|title=MSV holt Keeper Mark Flekken: Ehrgeizig, jung und hungrig!|date=12 June 2016|work=msv-duisburg.de|access-date=14 June 2016|archive-date=17 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617091437/http://msv-duisburg.de/main.asp?reiter=aktuelles_p&bgi=yes&mode=aktuell&aid=7311|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 7 August 2016, he scored a goal, after a corner, in a 1–1 draw against [[VfL Osnabrück]], when he went to the opposite box during the last minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rp-online.de/sport/fussball/dritteliga/msv-duisburg-torwart-mark-flekken-trifft-fuer-zebras-zum-11-aid-1.6168291|title=Torwart Flekken trifft für "Zebras" zum 1:1|date=7 August 2016|work=rp-online.de}}</ref> In February 2018, Flekken conceded a goal in a [[2. Bundesliga]] match against [[FC Ingolstadt 04|FC Ingolstadt]], when he turned his back on the play to take a drink from his water bottle.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/av/football/43187129|title=Keeper turns back on play to concede bizarre goal|work=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|date=26 February 2018|access-date=26 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Drinking Goalie - Funniest Goalkeeper Fail Ever?|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3GMig6o3bMs|language=en|access-date=26 May 2021}}</ref>

===SC Freiburg===
Flekken joined [[SC Freiburg]] for the [[2018–19 SC Freiburg season|2018–19 season]].<ref>{{cite press release|url=https://www.scfreiburg.com/news/mark-flekken-kommt-zum-sport-club|title= Mark Flekken kommt zum Sport-Club|publisher=[[SC Freiburg]]|date=14 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180515015349/https://www.scfreiburg.com/news/mark-flekken-kommt-zum-sport-club|archive-date=15 May 2018}}</ref> A backup to [[Alexander Schwolow]] throughout the season, he made his debut in the final matchday of the [[2018–19 Bundesliga|2018–19 season]] against [[1. FC Nürnberg]].<ref>{{cite news|title=5:1 - Freiburg feiert furiosen Saisonabschluss |url=https://www.kicker.de/freiburg-gegen-nuernberg-2019-bundesliga-4243567/analyse |work=kicker |date=18 May 2019 |language=de-DE}}</ref> After Schwolow's departure before the start of the [[2020–21 Bundesliga|2020–21 season]], he was appointed the new starter, but shortly after he suffered a complicated elbow injury while warming up for the [[DFB-Pokal]] match against [[SV Waldhof Mannheim]] which sidelined him for the entire season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Torwart Flekken fehlt Freiburg ein halbes Jahr |url=https://www.weltfussball.de/news/_n4172394_/torwart-flekken-fehlt-freiburg-ein-halbes-jahr/ |work=Weltfussball |date=17 September 2020 |language=de}}</ref> Meanwhile, he was replaced in goal by [[Florian Müller (footballer, born 1997)|Florian Müller]], who was on loan from [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]]. He returned as the starter in goal on 9 May 2021; before that he had regained match practice with the [[SC Freiburg II|Freiburg reserves]] in the [[Regionalliga Südwest]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Freiburg im Saisonendspurt mit Flekken im Tor |url=https://www.weltfussball.de/news/_n4454443_/freiburg-im-saisonendspurt-mit-flekken-im-tor/ |work=Weltfussball |date=7 May 2021 |language=de}}</ref>

Flekken started the [[2021–22 Bundesliga|2021–22 season]] as the undisputed first-choice goalkeeper and, after ten games in a row without defeat, saw the team in third place of the league, to which he had contributed with the league's best rate of shots saved.<ref>{{cite news |title=Die Zahlen hinter dem Erfolg: Was Freiburg so stark macht |url=https://www.kicker.de/die-zahlen-hinter-dem-erfolg-was-freiburg-so-stark-macht-877541/artikel |work=kicker |date=5 November 2021 |language=de-DE}}</ref>

===Brentford===
On 31 May 2023, Flekken signed for [[Premier League]] club [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]] for a reported fee of £11 million.<ref>{{cite news |title=Brentford sign keeper Mark Flekken from Freiburg |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/65763042 |access-date=31 May 2023 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=31 May 2023}}</ref>

====2023–24 season====
In his debut season, Flekken recorded seven clean sheets and made 113 saves, ranking eighth in both categories across the Premier League.<ref name="SeasonReview">{{cite web |title=Season Review: Top Performers |url=https://www.brentfordfc.com/en/news/article/analysis-brentford-player-of-the-season-premier-league-2023-24-season-review-part-3 |website=Brentford FC |access-date=7 May 2025}}</ref> He also stood out for his distribution, becoming one of only two goalkeepers in the league to register an assist, setting up a goal for [[Neal Maupay]] against [[Manchester City]]. He made four key passes, the most by any goalkeeper in the division that season.<ref name="SeasonReview" />

In February 2024, Flekken won the [[Premier League Save of the Month]] award for a reflex save against [[Pedro Neto]] of [[Wolverhampton Wanderers]]. The stop was later nominated for [[Premier League Save of the Season]].<ref name="SaveOfMonth">{{cite web |title=Flekken wins Save of the Month |url=https://www.brentfordfc.com/en/news/article/first-team-premier-league-save-of-the-month-february-mark-flekken-brentford |website=Brentford FC |access-date=7 May 2025}}</ref> His form across the campaign earned him a call-up to the Netherlands national team for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref name="PlayerProfile">{{cite web |title=Mark Flekken Player Profile |url=https://www.brentfordfc.com/en/teams/profile/mark-flekken |website=Brentford FC |access-date=7 May 2025}}</ref>

====2024–25 season====
In the [[2024–25 Premier League|2024–25 season]], he maintained a high level of performance and was named Brentford’s Player of the Month for February 2025 after conceding just one goal across three matches, including clean sheets in victories over [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] and [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref name="PotMFeb">{{cite web |title=Flekken wins February Player of the Month |url=https://www.brentfordfc.com/en/news/article/first-team-mark-flekken-brentford-aosom-player-of-the-month-february-2025 |website=Brentford FC |access-date=7 May 2025}}</ref> By April 2025, he had made more saves than any other goalkeeper in Europe’s top five leagues, with 103, and ranked eighth in the Premier League for save percentage at 72.5%.<ref name="TopFive">{{cite web |title=Top Five Players: Season Stats |url=https://www.brentfordfc.com/en/news/article/analysis-brentford-top-five-players-premier-league-2024-25 |website=Brentford FC |access-date=7 May 2025}}</ref> In addition, Flekken was rated as the fifth best goalkeeper in the world according to data from the CIES Football Observatory Index.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c3wxx1e6616o|title=Chelsea's Sanchez among world's best keepers, says data|date=11 April 2025|language=en}}</ref>

Upon the conclusion of the 2024–25 season, he led the Premier League in saves, making 153 with a save percentage of 73.6%.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/article/mark-flekken-set-join-erik-151600780.html |title=Mark Flekken set to join up with Erik Ten Hag at Bayer Leverkusen |publisher=Yahoo Sports |date=2 June 2025 }}</ref>

===Bayer Leverkusen===
On 3 June 2025, Flekken signed for [[Bundesliga]] club [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] on a three-year deal for a reported fee of around €10 million.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bayer 04 sign Netherlands keeper Mark Flekken from Brentford |url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/bayer-04-sign-netherlands-keeper-mark-flekken-from-brentford |date=3 June 2025 |access-date=3 June 2025 |publisher=Bayer 04 Leverkusen |language=en-gb}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Harris |first1=Jay |last2=Stafford-Bloor |first2=Sebastian |title=Bayer Leverkusen sign goalkeeper Mark Flekken from Brentford |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6397078/2025/06/03/mark-flekken-leverkusen-transfer/ |date=3 June 2025 |access-date=3 June 2025 |publisher=The Athletic |language=en-gb}}</ref>

==International career==
Flekken was called up to the senior [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]] squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches against [[Montenegro national football team|Montenegro]] and [[Norway national football team|Norway]] on 13 and 16 November 2021, respectively.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/nederlands-elftal/79760/van-gaal-roept-24-spelers-op-voor-laatste-groepsduels-wk-kwalificatie|title=Van Gaal roept 24 spelers op voor laatste groepsduels WK-kwalificatie|website=OnsOranje.nl |publisher=[[Royal Dutch Football Association]] |date=5 November 2021 |access-date=5 November 2021|language=nl}}</ref>

Flekken made his international debut for the Netherlands on 26 March 2022 in a friendly match against [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://eu-football.info/_match.php?id=18084|title=Netherlands vs Denmark, 26 March 2022|website=eu-football.info |date=26 March 2022 |access-date=8 September 2023|language=en}}</ref>

On 29 May 2024, Flekken was named in the Netherlands' squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5526712/2024/05/29/netherlands-euro-2024-squad-confirmed/|title=Example Title|date=29 May 2024|access-date=7 June 2024|website=The New York Times}}</ref>

